Berjaya Food, DRB, Petronas Chemicals: Malaysia Equity Preview

-- B y   C h a n   T i e n   H i n
-- 
2011-03-08T00:13:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/berjaya-food-drb-petronas-chemicals-malaysia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Malaysia trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The  FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI (FBMKLCI)  Index fell 0.5 percent to
1,515.74.  Berjaya Food Bhd. (BFD MK): The operator of the Kenny
Rogers Roasters restaurant chain in Malaysia will make its
listing debut. The company sold shares at 51 sen each, according
to its prospectus dated Feb. 18.        DRB-Hicom Bhd. (DRB)  : The automotive assembler said it
won a 7.55 billion-ringgit ($2.5 billion) contract to supply the
Southeast Asian nation’s government with armored vehicles. The
contract to supply 257 vehicles is for a period of seven years,
the company said in a statement. DRB-Hicom gained 2.2 percent to
1.85 ringgit.        Petronas Chemicals Group Bhd. (PCHEM)  : The Employees
Provident Fund, Malaysia’s largest pension fund, bought 11.9
million shares in the petrochemicals arm of state oil and gas
company Petroliam Nasional Bhd., a stock filing showed. Petronas
Chemicals gained 0.2 percent to 6.34 ringgit.        Sunway Holdings Bhd. (SGW)  : The construction and
property group won a 74.1 million-ringgit building contract from
Malaysian Bio-XCell Sdn., according to a company statement.
Sunway rose 0.9 percent to 2.20 ringgit.  To contact the reporter on this story:
